			<node ID="ID_681766882" TEXT="Second-order logic is an extension of first-order logic where in addition to quantifiers such as &#8220;for every object (in the universe of discourse)&#8221; one has quantifiers such as &#8220;for every property of objects (in the universe of discourse).&#8221; This augmentation of the language increases its expressive strength without adding new non-logical symbols such as new predicate symbols." />
