			<node ID="ID_533133472" TEXT="A semantic network or net is a graph structure for representing knowledge in patterns of interconnected nodes and arcs. Computer implementations of semantic networks were first developed for artificial intelligence and machine translation but earlier versions have long been used in philosophy psychology and linguistics." />
